1
00:01:30,550 --> 00:01:34,970
[Deep Lurk]

2
00:01:35,410 --> 00:01:38,020
[Episode 34]

3
00:02:04,430 --> 00:02:05,910
Looking at these dossiers,

4
00:02:05,990 --> 00:02:07,920
Yun Hongshen became increasingly certain—

5
00:02:08,310 --> 00:02:10,110
Kunwu wasn't Ling Han,

6
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:11,670
but someone else.

7
00:02:12,350 --> 00:02:13,670
As more details

8
00:02:13,690 --> 00:02:15,070
unfolded before his eyes,

9
00:02:15,100 --> 00:02:17,060
the doubts and evidence

10
00:02:17,630 --> 00:02:19,070
all pointed in one direction—

11
00:02:19,190 --> 00:02:21,230
Ke Jingping.

12
00:02:21,630 --> 00:02:23,710
The likelihood of him being Kunwu

13
00:02:23,880 --> 00:02:24,860
was the highest.

14
00:02:27,510 --> 00:02:28,950
Shengxingcai...

15
00:02:29,430 --> 00:02:30,840
Shengxing...

16
00:02:31,230 --> 00:02:32,140
Shengxing Hotel.

17
00:02:32,890 --> 00:02:34,829
The inn where Myna stayed after returning to Changsha.

18
00:03:36,270 --> 00:03:40,620
[Bureau of Investigation and Statistics]

19
00:03:49,110 --> 00:03:49,950
You don't have to wait for me.

20
00:03:51,820 --> 00:03:52,800
I'm fine now.

21
00:03:52,870 --> 00:03:54,310
I just had a moment of reflection.

22
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:56,070
About Ling Han,

23
00:03:56,890 --> 00:03:58,090
the Chief did his best.

24
00:03:59,790 --> 00:04:01,630
He has his reasons. Don't blame him.

25
00:04:01,990 --> 00:04:03,830
If you're feeling frustrated, just say it.

26
00:04:03,950 --> 00:04:05,070
Don't bottle it all up.

27
00:04:05,950 --> 00:04:07,580
Even if venting doesn't solve the problem,

28
00:04:07,870 --> 00:04:09,910
it might lighten the weight

29
00:04:10,390 --> 00:04:11,830
on your chest.

30
00:04:11,830 --> 00:04:12,510
Right?

31
00:04:14,350 --> 00:04:16,230
If she knew the truth,

32
00:04:16,990 --> 00:04:18,070
how painful would it be for her?

33
00:04:21,829 --> 00:04:22,630
Yun Hongshen?

34
00:04:35,990 --> 00:04:37,230
It will all pass.

35
00:05:09,310 --> 00:05:10,110
Head upstairs.

36
00:05:10,150 --> 00:05:10,950
Sleep early.

37
00:05:11,990 --> 00:05:13,320
Okay, let me ask you.

38
00:05:13,460 --> 00:05:15,430
Have you ever suspected that Yun Hongshen might be a Communist?

39
00:05:15,870 --> 00:05:16,750
What would you do

40
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:18,950
if it were me?

41
00:05:21,430 --> 00:05:23,160
And what if I ultimately decide

42
00:05:24,350 --> 00:05:25,390
to follow the Chief?

43
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:29,990
What would you do?

44
00:05:30,940 --> 00:05:32,159
Did he say anything to you?

45
00:05:33,430 --> 00:05:34,120
Nothing.

46
00:05:36,070 --> 00:05:37,470
He's just a little disappointed.

47
00:05:41,110 --> 00:05:42,670
You can't bear his disappointment,

48
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:44,550
can you?

49
00:05:47,710 --> 00:05:48,870
Walk with me for a while.

50
00:06:00,190 --> 00:06:01,950
He isn't someone who shows warmth easily.

51
00:06:03,790 --> 00:06:05,870
But over the years,

52
00:06:07,430 --> 00:06:09,110
he tried to be a brother to me—

53
00:06:10,030 --> 00:06:11,390
even a father figure.

54
00:06:12,830 --> 00:06:14,150
When I struggled with my studies,

55
00:06:14,510 --> 00:06:16,230
he'd help, no matter how exhausted he was.

56
00:06:17,110 --> 00:06:18,070
When I got hurt,

57
00:06:19,110 --> 00:06:20,350
he'd buy medicine for me.

58
00:06:21,310 --> 00:06:23,150
When my bluntness offended people,

59
00:06:24,430 --> 00:06:25,910
he'd quietly smooth things over.

60
00:06:27,270 --> 00:06:29,170
Last year, I suffered a serious gunshot wound

61
00:06:29,190 --> 00:06:30,710
and was unconscious for over ten hours.

62
00:06:33,510 --> 00:06:35,750
He waited outside the operating room the entire time.

63
00:06:38,710 --> 00:06:40,110
I'm not just grateful to him.

64
00:06:42,430 --> 00:06:44,390
I've spent ten years by his side.

65
00:06:46,710 --> 00:06:48,230
I see him as my family.

66
00:06:50,909 --> 00:06:51,710
I understand.

67
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:54,310
Ever since you lost your family,

68
00:06:54,909 --> 00:06:56,480
he's been your emotional anchor.

69
00:06:59,860 --> 00:07:01,370
But the way he looked at me earlier...

70
00:07:04,550 --> 00:07:06,740
When he said, "I'm disappointed in you,"

71
00:07:10,350 --> 00:07:11,710
I couldn't handle it.

72
00:07:14,310 --> 00:07:15,110
You see.

73
00:07:16,710 --> 00:07:18,980
I'm not as strong as you think I am.

74
00:07:20,990 --> 00:07:22,470
I have my weaknesses too.

75
00:07:26,110 --> 00:07:27,260
That's not a weakness.

76
00:07:29,860 --> 00:07:30,950
That's loyalty to your feelings.

77
00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:39,560
No matter which direction we choose,

78
00:07:41,670 --> 00:07:43,700
as long as we reach the same destination in the end,

79
00:07:43,730 --> 00:07:44,640
it's enough.

80
00:07:47,150 --> 00:07:49,230
Does the path we take really matter?

81
00:07:59,540 --> 00:08:00,630
If you take the wrong path,

82
00:08:02,310 --> 00:08:04,150
you might never reach the destination.

83
00:08:05,150 --> 00:08:06,110
Some choices,

84
00:08:06,980 --> 00:08:08,110
if wrong from the start,

85
00:08:08,190 --> 00:08:09,820
can't lead to the same ending.

86
00:08:12,940 --> 00:08:14,670
But no matter what happens, I'll walk this path with you.

87
00:08:16,150 --> 00:08:17,550
How can you be so sure

88
00:08:20,350 --> 00:08:21,980
the path you've chosen is the right one?

89
00:08:24,070 --> 00:08:26,070
You already know the answer,

90
00:08:27,130 --> 00:08:27,620
don't you?

91
00:08:31,230 --> 00:08:32,030
Alright.

92
00:08:32,110 --> 00:08:32,970
It's getting late.

93
00:08:33,070 --> 00:08:33,820
You should go home now.

94
00:08:35,309 --> 00:08:37,110
Take your time with this decision.

95
00:08:37,710 --> 00:08:38,510
Think it through

96
00:08:39,039 --> 00:08:40,429
carefully.

97
00:08:42,630 --> 00:08:43,710
This time,

98
00:08:47,430 --> 00:08:49,580
I hope you can live for yourself

99
00:08:51,070 --> 00:08:51,870
and walk a path

100
00:08:53,430 --> 00:08:54,790
that's truly worth taking.

101
00:09:02,270 --> 00:09:03,070
Second Young Master,

102
00:09:04,270 --> 00:09:05,150
you're back.

103
00:09:05,590 --> 00:09:06,270
Where is my brother?

104
00:09:06,350 --> 00:09:07,070
In his room.

105
00:09:19,590 --> 00:09:20,390
I'm back.

106
00:09:20,390 --> 00:09:21,190
How did it go?

107
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:22,350
Did you catch him?

108
00:09:24,150 --> 00:09:25,070
Ling Han is dead.

109
00:09:25,660 --> 00:09:26,950
Mi Lan and Zong Fang have escaped.

110
00:09:36,110 --> 00:09:36,910
Hongqi,

111
00:09:38,310 --> 00:09:39,390
can you stay down?

112
00:09:45,390 --> 00:09:46,070
You two talk.

113
00:09:46,490 --> 00:09:47,640
I'll go replace Dao.

114
00:09:59,190 --> 00:10:00,270
How are you feeling today?

115
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:01,200
Any better?

116
00:10:01,550 --> 00:10:02,350
Much better.

117
00:10:03,230 --> 00:10:04,230
You should rest more,

118
00:10:04,670 --> 00:10:05,710
so you can recover quickly.

119
00:10:06,110 --> 00:10:06,750
By the way,

120
00:10:08,150 --> 00:10:10,340
after dinner, I dozed off for a bit.

121
00:10:10,340 --> 00:10:11,710
But I couldn't sleep soundly.

122
00:10:11,830 --> 00:10:12,820
I kept waking up.

123
00:10:13,150 --> 00:10:14,830
I had this strange feeling like someone was walking outside.

124
00:10:15,590 --> 00:10:17,040
Probably my brother and Dao

125
00:10:17,070 --> 00:10:18,150
made some noise

126
00:10:18,390 --> 00:10:20,000
while taking turns to keep watch.

127
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:22,230
Their footsteps are pretty distinct,

128
00:10:22,630 --> 00:10:24,060
but it didn't quite feel like them.

129
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:25,950
Maybe I was just imagining things.

130
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:27,830
Anyway,

131
00:10:29,590 --> 00:10:30,990
why couldn't you save Ling Han?

132
00:10:31,790 --> 00:10:33,230
Ke Jingping was monitoring him personally.

133
00:10:33,790 --> 00:10:34,950
There was no way to intervene.

134
00:10:35,830 --> 00:10:36,870
Before Ling Han died,

135
00:10:37,230 --> 00:10:39,190
I told him the truth about his origins.

136
00:10:39,190 --> 00:10:40,390
You did your best.

137
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:41,350
You have no reason

138
00:10:42,110 --> 00:10:43,620
to blame yourself.

139
00:10:44,030 --> 00:10:45,670
Since the Organization has confirmed

140
00:10:45,710 --> 00:10:46,910
that Kunwu is someone else,

141
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:49,470
then the person with the most control over this entire situation,

142
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:51,550
the one pulling all the strings is Ke Jingping.

143
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:52,870
Your suspicions

144
00:10:52,870 --> 00:10:53,900
were right.

145
00:10:56,270 --> 00:10:58,200
He's terrifying—

146
00:10:58,870 --> 00:11:00,590
manipulating everything from the shadows,

147
00:11:01,190 --> 00:11:03,430
toying with everyone in his grasp.

148
00:11:03,510 --> 00:11:05,080
Even Ling Han, someone so skilled,

149
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:06,470
ended up being his scapegoat.

150
00:11:07,220 --> 00:11:08,420
What's more terrifying

151
00:11:08,990 --> 00:11:11,110
is how flawlessly he's hidden it all.

152
00:11:12,830 --> 00:11:15,190
If the Organization hadn't uncovered

153
00:11:15,190 --> 00:11:16,310
Ling Han's true identity,

154
00:11:17,270 --> 00:11:18,870
we'd all still be fooled by him.

155
00:11:19,290 --> 00:11:22,130
If Zong Fang hadn't forged that false background for Ling Han

156
00:11:22,150 --> 00:11:23,240
and dragged him into this mess,

157
00:11:25,150 --> 00:11:26,070
his life

158
00:11:27,910 --> 00:11:29,670
could've been so different.

159
00:11:34,310 --> 00:11:36,140
Ke Jingping is a formidable opponent.

160
00:11:38,310 --> 00:11:39,120
Secretary Wu,

161
00:11:39,830 --> 00:11:43,190
I suspect Ling Han may have left something for me

162
00:11:43,210 --> 00:11:44,490
at Shengxing Hotel.

163
00:11:46,950 --> 00:11:49,630
That would suggest he had something he wanted you to take care of.

164
00:11:51,030 --> 00:11:51,870
I think so.

165
00:11:54,070 --> 00:11:55,470
Though Ling Han wasn't Kunwu,

166
00:11:55,990 --> 00:11:58,020
he certainly did his share of bad deeds.

167
00:11:59,070 --> 00:12:00,070
If he left something behind,

168
00:12:00,070 --> 00:12:01,470
it could be a trap.

169
00:12:03,230 --> 00:12:05,030
When I saw him this afternoon,

170
00:12:05,470 --> 00:12:06,750
I hinted that

171
00:12:07,590 --> 00:12:09,390
I knew he wasn't Kunwu.

172
00:12:10,190 --> 00:12:11,470
He seemed to understand.

173
00:12:11,710 --> 00:12:13,350
The fewer mistakes you make,

174
00:12:13,670 --> 00:12:14,710
the more options you have.

175
00:12:15,150 --> 00:12:16,470
Sometimes, a slip of thought

176
00:12:16,990 --> 00:12:18,270
can lead to an entirely different outcome.

177
00:12:20,990 --> 00:12:22,700
Ling Han is meticulous in his actions.

178
00:12:23,390 --> 00:12:25,270
After he fell out with Ke Jingping

179
00:12:25,310 --> 00:12:27,520
and made such a bold move to seize the codebook,

180
00:12:27,670 --> 00:12:29,240
he must have had a backup plan.

181
00:12:30,020 --> 00:12:31,300
If he got the codebook,

182
00:12:31,670 --> 00:12:32,950
he would have had more leverage

183
00:12:32,950 --> 00:12:34,280
to go head-to-head with Ke Jingping.

184
00:12:34,430 --> 00:12:35,310
But if he failed

185
00:12:35,310 --> 00:12:36,900
or died at Ke Jingping's hands,

186
00:12:37,070 --> 00:12:37,840
Ling Han

187
00:12:38,880 --> 00:12:40,320
would have left behind

188
00:12:40,790 --> 00:12:42,620
something to expose Ke Jingping.

189
00:12:45,670 --> 00:12:49,870
If the thing he left

190
00:12:50,230 --> 00:12:52,830
can prove Ke Jingping is Kunwu...

191
00:12:56,390 --> 00:12:58,360
If Ling Han had anything left behind,

192
00:12:58,710 --> 00:13:00,990
it would be a clue, not direct evidence.

193
00:13:01,390 --> 00:13:03,070
But a clue is better than nothing.

194
00:13:03,630 --> 00:13:05,550
He likely realized Ke Jingping was a threat

195
00:13:05,550 --> 00:13:06,350
long before I did.

196
00:13:06,350 --> 00:13:08,240
If we continue digging,

197
00:13:08,310 --> 00:13:10,190
we should uncover something sooner or later.

198
00:13:10,430 --> 00:13:13,700
Then everything falls into place.

199
00:13:14,470 --> 00:13:15,470
For both personal and professional reasons,

200
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:17,840
you won't let Ke Jingping off the hook.

201
00:13:18,230 --> 00:13:19,390
If you have it,

202
00:13:19,390 --> 00:13:21,350
you can make the most use of it.

203
00:13:21,870 --> 00:13:22,870
I didn't expect

204
00:13:23,510 --> 00:13:24,840
you two, as rivals,

205
00:13:24,870 --> 00:13:27,470
would join forces in this way.

206
00:13:28,110 --> 00:13:29,350
But I haven't retrieved the item yet.

207
00:13:30,790 --> 00:13:31,950
I suspect Ke Jingping

208
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:33,150
already knew

209
00:13:33,180 --> 00:13:34,880
that I was starting to doubt him.

210
00:13:36,870 --> 00:13:38,910
He's much more dangerous than Ling Han ever was.

211
00:13:40,910 --> 00:13:42,230
Why do you think so?

212
00:13:42,990 --> 00:13:44,670
He asked me a question this afternoon.

213
00:13:47,550 --> 00:13:49,390
Also, when you went to rescue those children—

214
00:13:49,390 --> 00:13:51,230
you knew it was a trap set by Ling Han,

215
00:13:51,230 --> 00:13:52,830
but you still walked right into it.

216
00:13:54,550 --> 00:13:55,950
Why didn't you take the key

217
00:13:56,510 --> 00:13:58,080
back to the station first?

218
00:13:58,430 --> 00:13:59,310
If you and Wen Yeming

219
00:13:59,310 --> 00:14:00,670
had fallen into his hands,

220
00:14:00,670 --> 00:14:02,160
the safety would have been compromised.

221
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:06,310
Weren't you worried that Ling Han would get this codebook?

222
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:09,350
I managed to

223
00:14:09,470 --> 00:14:11,240
cover up his suspicion,

224
00:14:12,470 --> 00:14:13,780
but I still worry.

225
00:14:14,190 --> 00:14:14,910
Ke Jingping wouldn't ask me

226
00:14:14,910 --> 00:14:16,510
such a question for no reason.

227
00:14:16,540 --> 00:14:18,000
If he wants to take action against you,

228
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,110
he wouldn't wait—

229
00:14:19,310 --> 00:14:20,470
he'd move immediately.

230
00:14:20,750 --> 00:14:22,230
And Myna's codebook...

231
00:14:23,270 --> 00:14:24,830
He has the cipher key already,

232
00:14:24,830 --> 00:14:26,990
and now he has the codebook.

233
00:14:27,390 --> 00:14:29,070
If he destroys these two things

234
00:14:29,070 --> 00:14:30,350
or tampers with them,

235
00:14:30,630 --> 00:14:31,750
we will never get

236
00:14:31,750 --> 00:14:33,510
this precious information.

237
00:14:34,310 --> 00:14:35,470
I know what the cipher key is.

238
00:14:36,980 --> 00:14:39,820
Live to death...

239
00:14:40,340 --> 00:14:41,140
Year Nine...

240
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:45,650
Flowers in the Mirror.

241
00:14:51,010 --> 00:14:52,570
The Flowers in the Mirror of the Ninth Year in the Republic of China.

242
00:14:55,650 --> 00:14:56,600
This is the cipher key.

243
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:00,640
Great!

244
00:15:01,010 --> 00:15:02,170
Get you through right away.

245
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:13,560
Report!

246
00:15:13,970 --> 00:15:15,010
Sir, urgent telegram.

247
00:15:17,350 --> 00:15:18,430
Commander, the telegram.

248
00:15:30,310 --> 00:15:32,350
Due to the unique terrain of Changsha,

249
00:15:32,570 --> 00:15:35,290
the routes for the Japanese sneak attack are no more than two.

250
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:36,130
First,

251
00:15:36,510 --> 00:15:38,670
westward via the Yueyang Lake direction.

252
00:15:38,750 --> 00:15:41,550
Second, eastward via the Jiangxi direction.

253
00:15:42,910 --> 00:15:44,470
The combat strength of the Ninth War Zone is limited;

254
00:15:44,780 --> 00:15:46,550
there are only so many elite units.

255
00:15:46,910 --> 00:15:48,500
They can't attack from both east and west.

256
00:15:48,790 --> 00:15:50,750
With this precise intelligence,

257
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:54,320
our losses can be significantly reduced.

258
00:15:58,110 --> 00:15:58,910
Secretary Wu,

259
00:15:59,310 --> 00:16:00,310
something feels off.

260
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:05,550
Dad was still the same as before,

261
00:16:06,650 --> 00:16:08,190
always hiding a new bill

262
00:16:08,780 --> 00:16:10,110
inside a stack of old ones.

263
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:19,080
Movies are just for fun;

264
00:16:19,590 --> 00:16:21,230
you don't need to take it so seriously.

265
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,560
But she acted so well.

266
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:24,960
It felt so real.

267
00:16:30,040 --> 00:16:35,470
[Go south secretly]
[Evade the army defense]
[Sneak attack Changsha]

268
00:16:30,040 --> 00:16:35,470
[6th, 13th, and 33rd Divisions to lead the frontal assault; the 3rd Division to cross Yueyang Lake from the west]

269
00:16:37,510 --> 00:16:38,310
Off?

270
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:41,210
There's something wrong with this information.

271
00:16:52,430 --> 00:16:54,790
Yun Hongshen might be suspicious of my identity.

272
00:16:57,670 --> 00:16:58,670
Are you sure?

273
00:16:58,950 --> 00:17:00,240
It's just a hunch.

274
00:17:00,700 --> 00:17:02,490
This afternoon, he took the key to meet Ling Han.

275
00:17:02,510 --> 00:17:03,690
That's highly suspicious.

276
00:17:04,910 --> 00:17:06,510
Tonight's operation at the church—

277
00:17:06,510 --> 00:17:07,970
he didn't want me on the scene.

278
00:17:08,079 --> 00:17:09,520
Before he left the station,

279
00:17:09,660 --> 00:17:11,540
he secretly went to the archive room.

280
00:17:11,589 --> 00:17:13,500
I'm not sure what he found out,

281
00:17:13,829 --> 00:17:15,290
but these small details

282
00:17:15,349 --> 00:17:16,660
make me suspect

283
00:17:18,150 --> 00:17:20,000
that he's growing suspicious of me.

